<subSubSection id="A8D5656DA702D66E798D6C1EDC1241AD" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E798D6C1EDE06417F" blockId="14.[189,310,819,845]" box="[189,310,819,845]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
<heading id="BB38818AA702D66E798D6C1EDE06417F" bold="true" box="[189,310,819,845]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A702D66E798D6C1EDE06417F" bold="true" box="[189,310,819,845]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E798D6C4FDC1241AD" blockId="14.[189,1398,866,928]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
This species is distinguishable by the distinctive double-lobed PLP and short and hook-shaped embolus tip directed in a clockwise path (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A702D66E7B0A6CA8DD8E41AD" box="[570,702,901,927]" captionStart="Fig 8" captionStartId="15.[189,230,1913,1939]" captionTargetBox="[287,1301,265,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-14@15.[287,1301,265,1861]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig 8. Carrhotus lobatus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Palp, C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–D = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518325" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518325/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Figs 8C–D</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A702D66E7BFA6CA8DC2541AD" box="[714,789,901,927]" captionStart="Fig 9" captionStartId="16.[189,230,1913,1939]" captionTargetBox="[216,1331,819,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[204,1383,799,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig 9. Carrhotus lobatus sp. nov., palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; TE = tegulum. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518329" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518329/files/figure.png" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">9A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8D5656DA702D66E798D6CEADDAE4600" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E798D6CEADE7441D3" blockId="14.[189,324,967,993]" box="[189,324,967,993]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
<heading id="BB38818AA702D66E798D6CEADE7441D3" bold="true" box="[189,324,967,993]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A702D66E798D6CEADE7441D3" bold="true" box="[189,324,967,993]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E798D6CD8DDAE4600" blockId="14.[189,1399,1013,1074]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
The specific epithet is derived from the Latin word ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="27CF4D65A702D66E7A036CD8DCB9463D" authorityName="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2022" box="[819,905,1013,1039]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobatus">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A702D66E7A036CD8DCB9463D" box="[819,905,1013,1039]" italics="true" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">lobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’ meaning ‘lobed’, loosely referring to its distinctive proximal lobe of the tegulum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
