<subSubSection id="A8D5656DA702D670798D6965DA064069" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" type="description">
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E798D6965DE7E4450" blockId="14.[189,334,1608,1634]" box="[189,334,1608,1634]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
<heading id="BB38818AA702D66E798D6965DE7E4450" bold="true" box="[189,334,1608,1634]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="14" pageNumber="92" reason="3">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A702D66E798D6965DE7E4450" bold="true" box="[189,334,1608,1634]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E79DA695ADE1A44A3" blockId="14.[188,1399,1655,1822]" box="[234,298,1655,1681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A702D66E79DA695ADE1A44A3" bold="true" box="[234,298,1655,1681]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">Male</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D66E798D69B7DBEC452F" blockId="14.[188,1399,1655,1822]" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">MEASUREMENTS. TL 5.15, PL 2.13, PW at PLEs 1.71, AL 2.19, AW 1.71. Eye field: diameter of AME 0.46; ALE 0.28; PME 0.08; PLE 0.26; PME–PME 1.46; PLE–PLE 1.34; ALE–PME 0.24; ALE–PLE 0.6. Leg I: Tr 0.82, Fm 1.08, Pt 1.36, Tb 0.86, Mt 0.5; Leg II: Tr 0.7, Fm 0.82, Pt 0.8, Tb 0.6, Mt 0.4; Leg III: Tr 1, Fm 0.9, Pt 0.74, Tb 0.8, Mt 0.44; Leg IV: Tr 0.92, Fm 0.5, Pt 1.08, Tb 0.74, Mt 0.46.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A702D670798D6868DD5343E1" blockId="14.[188,1401,1861,1993]" lastBlockId="16.[189,1400,265,467]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="94" pageId="14" pageNumber="92">
COLOR AND BODY. In ethanol, carapace brown, posterior region blackish-brown. Clypeal region brown; ALEs and PLEs surrounded by blackish orbital setae. Lateral margins of carapace slightly truncated and steep. Chelicerae brownish with curved outer margins and excavated inner margins: two promarginal and one retromarginal teeth. Sternum pentagonal, blackish brown; labium and maxillae brown. Leg I robust; femora I–IV dark brown dorsally; patellae and tibiae dark brown; tarsi and metatarsi of all legs dark brown. Abdomen oblong, sparsely covered with black hairs; anterior margin covered with long black scales with sparse white hairs making an arc; no prominent pattern present on posterior region, beige pairs of transverse lines and pair of beige spots covered with white hairs on mid dorsum; venter blackish brown with a blackish brown median region. Spinnerets blackish brown, covered with a patch of white hairs dorsally (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A71CD67078E46E94DD6643E1" box="[468,598,441,467]" captionStart="Fig 8" captionStartId="15.[189,230,1913,1939]" captionTargetBox="[287,1301,265,1861]" captionTargetId="figure-14@15.[287,1301,265,1861]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="Fig 8. Carrhotus lobatus sp. nov. A–B. Male habitus. A. Dorsal view. B. Ventral view. C–D. Palp, C. Ventral view. D. Retrolateral view. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–D = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518325" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518325/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">Fig. 8A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<caption id="B4B0666EA703D66F798D6854DBCB45E8" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518325" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6518325" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518325/files/figure.png" pageId="15" pageNumber="93" startId="15.[189,230,1913,1939]" targetBox="[287,1301,265,1861]" targetPageId="15">
<paragraph id="E07036E6A703D66F798D6854DBCB45E8" blockId="15.[189,1398,1913,2010]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F798D6854DE3745A1" bold="true" box="[189,263,1913,1939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">Fig 8.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="27CF4D65A703D66F78226854DEDB45A1" authority="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin, 2022" authorityName="Satkunanathan &amp; Benjamin" authorityYear="2022" box="[274,491,1913,1939]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Carrhotus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="15" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lobatus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F78226854DEDB45A1" box="[274,491,1913,1939]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">Carrhotus lobatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="C988578FA703D66F78C66854DD6445A1" box="[502,596,1913,1939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F7B6F6854DDA745A1" bold="true" box="[607,663,1913,1939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">A–B</emphasis>
. Male habitus. 
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F7A676854DC5C45A1" bold="true" box="[855,876,1913,1939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">A</emphasis>
. Dorsal view. 
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F7D116854DB0545A1" bold="true" box="[1057,1077,1913,1939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">B</emphasis>
. Ventral view. 
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F7DC06854DA1845A1" bold="true" box="[1264,1320,1913,1939]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">C–D</emphasis>
. Palp, 
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F798D68B1DFE24584" bold="true" box="[189,210,1948,1974]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">C</emphasis>
. Ventral view. 
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A703D66F78B668B1DEAB4584" bold="true" box="[390,411,1948,1974]" pageId="15" pageNumber="93">D</emphasis>
. Retrolateral view. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; TE = tegulum. Scale bars: A–B = 2 mm; C–D = 0.2 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A71CD670798D6ED6DA064069" blockId="16.[189,1399,506,604]" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">
PALP. Dark brown; embolus short and hook-shaped and embolus tip directed in the clockwise path; its base separated from the tegulum. The double-lobed PLP is very distinctive compared to that of the other species considered here. RTA long and angle between the RTA and tibia is about 45º (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A71CD6707D986D6CDA1A4069" box="[1192,1322,577,603]" captionStart="Fig 9" captionStartId="16.[189,230,1913,1939]" captionTargetBox="[216,1331,819,1856]" captionTargetId="figure-188@16.[204,1383,799,1873]" captionTargetPageId="16" captionText="Fig 9. Carrhotus lobatus sp. nov., palp. A. Ventral view. B. Retrolateral view. Abbreviations: E = embolus; PLP = posterior lateral protrusion; RTA = retrolateral tibial apophysis; TE = tegulum. Scale bars = 0.2 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518329" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518329/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">Fig. 9A–B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A8D5656DA71CD670798D6DAFDA4240DD" pageId="16" pageNumber="94" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="E07036E6A71CD670798D6DAFDEDE40AE" blockId="16.[189,494,642,668]" box="[189,494,642,668]" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">
<heading id="BB38818AA71CD670798D6DAFDEDE40AE" bold="true" box="[189,494,642,668]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="16" pageNumber="94" reason="3">
<emphasis id="D2BBEAF4A71CD670798D6DAFDEDE40AE" bold="true" box="[189,494,642,668]" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E07036E6A71CD670798D6D9CDA4240DD" blockId="16.[189,1398,689,751]" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">
This species occurs in the montane and submontane forests of the central highlands of 
<collectingCountry id="98D87676A71CD6707DF66D9CDA0940F9" box="[1222,1337,689,715]" name="Sri Lanka" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">Sri Lanka</collectingCountry>
with limited distribution (
<figureCitation id="78F42A63A71CD67078806DF9DD3740DC" box="[432,519,724,750]" captionStart="Fig 17" captionStartId="28.[189,230,1982,2008]" captionTargetBox="[189,1382,719,1923]" captionTargetId="figure-115@28.[189,1397,718,1944]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="Fig 17. Distribution of Carrhotus spp. of Sri Lanka." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6518352" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6518352/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="94">Fig. 17</figureCitation>
). Specimens were collected by beating vegetation up to a height of 
<quantity id="27379B03A71CD6707C106DF9DA5D40DD" box="[1312,1389,724,751]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="16" pageNumber="94" unit="m" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">
1– 
<specimenCount id="F6C9FD6FA71CD6707C0C6DF9DA5D40DD" box="[1340,1389,724,751]" pageId="16" pageNumber="94" type="generic">2 m</specimenCount>
</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
